!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

obvious /ˈɒbvɪəs/

1. ADJ If something is obvious , it is easy to see or understand. 明显的 

例： ...the need to rectify what is an obvious injustice. …纠正明显不公行为的必要性。 

2. ADJ If you describe something that someone says as obvious , you are being critical of it because you think it is unnecessary or shows lack of imagination. 无新意的 [表不满] 

例： Such an explanation seems too simple, and too obvious. 这样的一个解释似乎太简单而且太没新意。 

3. PHRASE If you say that someone is stating the obvious , you mean that they are saying something that everyone already knows and understands. 说人人皆知的事

</div>

